<br>
At level 16, everything I am wearing now was bought from the druid guild at Kelethin.  Since then, I cannot find/loot anything better than what I have now.  At East Commonland, the auction channel is alway full of superb items for sell, but there is no way I can afford any of them.<br>
<br>
I have been also working on my tailoring skill, but still not up to par yet to make any leather armor for myself.<br>
<br>
So, I am looking for some recommendation and suggestion how I can upgrade my armor, or is it necessary for me to do that at this current level?<br>
<br>
Thank you for your input in advance.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/26/01 10:07:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> One of the nice things about being a druid is that we are not really that dependent on equipment compaired with melee and hybrid classes.  When I was 16 I was wearing a mix of patchwork leather and storebought leather and I managed pretty well (I still wore cloth in some places till I was 14).  My first non-leather purchases were some silver jasper rings.  They weren't very expensive, something like 4pp each.  Eventually I also got some electrum jasper earrings and a savant cap for my head.  I don't think all that ran me more than 50pp all totaled.  Somewhere in there I picked up some split paw gloves for about 25pp.  My first &quot;major&quot; purchase was a silver ruby veil, which I guess might run for 150pp these days?  Getting your wisdom up doesn't matter that much anyways untill your mid 30s when you'd need the extra mana for quad kiting or killing hill giants, which are things you can avoid anyways.<br>
<br>
Since you're a wood elf, you should look into the Tunarian symbol quests the Felwithe clerics give out.  The quests result in some very nice neck items.  Heck, the 3rd symbol in the series is better than what I'm wearing now.<br>
<br>
Now that I think about it, 16 might also be old enough to quest for a Testament of Vanear.  The mob you'd be camping is also 16, so you might want to get a friend (a really good friend) to camp it with you.  It involves a long (up to 8 hours) camp but the prize is a nice 10 wis 10 mana book for your offhand. <p><hr>
Norpin Bramblebum<br>
Halfling Druid of the 42nd Season<br>
Erollisi Marr Server<br>
Guaranteed 100% E-Bay free.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A> at: 10/28/01 7:15:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umetsa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Metsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/27/01 7:28:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> Hi, I'm just adding a quick post to try to avert some problems later...... the previous post was right, I wore patchwork until into my early 20's...... and yeah get the most wisdom equipment that you can afford, over armor and even better weapons.  However, while the testament of Vanear is a great idea, do a bunch of research on it first. When you kill Dyllan, you take a HUGE faction hit with the corrupt Qeynos guards.  If you weren't careful up to then, you WILL be KOS to the corrupt guards.  So do some faction work first to soften the blow on that hit.  I'd recommend the Jenam and Rebby quest in Freeport, which can be found in quests on Alakazam (or however it's spelled)  So happy hunting !<br>
<br>
 <p>Metsa ! The Original Evil Unwashed Druid!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uradonnoble.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radon Noble</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.vrconcept.com/radon/icons/ff9.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/27/01 3:34:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> Yes, I have done some research on the ToV.  I know Dyllan is at around lvl 16, but I also gotta be careful with the smugglers around him as they are all red.  <br>
<br>
I also read about the faction hit... but just courious how many times I should do the Jenam and Rebby quests?  I have done that 3-4 times just trying to soften my faction with the Military guards at East Freeport and West Commandland.... I was planning to do the Orc Pick / Cutthroat Insignia Ring quest.... but I know it is very hard to lower the faction with the Jenam and Rebby quest.... I am still apprehensive to those guards at freeport. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/28/01 7:13:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> Took me 20 trips to go from apprehensive to indifferent with the FP guards I think.  You get much bigger hits with the tradesfolk though, they love me now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uradonnoble.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radon Noble</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.vrconcept.com/radon/icons/ff9.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/29/01 10:33:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> Thank you, Norpin.  What is it all about &quot;tradefolk&quot;?  Could you please give me a little bit more detail? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thorvold>Thorvold</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/29/01 3:08:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Question - How to get better armor?</span><hr size=1> For a better way to offset the CorruptQeynosGuards hit, do the Crate quest(evil) 4 times.  It starts in NQeynos with Guard Weleth at the gate, runs to Nessiff in SQeynos near the clock tower, and back to Lt. Dagarok near the Priest of Discord.  With SOW, it can be run in 1-2 minutes with 2 zone loads.  The quest gives +25 faction points per trip, and the hit for killing Dyllin is -100.  To do this quest, you need indifferent faction with QeynosGuards and CorruptQeynosGuards, or sneak/hide to get it.<br>
<br>
With this quest I got to warmly before I killed Dyllin, killing him dropped me to Kindly, and doing it 4 times got me back to warmly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3460.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3433.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3469.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3469.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3469.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3469.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests"